The paper discusses the vulnerability of AI agents to deception in games, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of cognitive biases to exploit deception suggests a connection to game theory (cs.GT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of VGDL and GVGAI frameworks suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
